Class PhotoController

  • java.lang.Object
    • controller.PhotoController
  • public class PhotoController
extends java.lang.Object
    This class takes care of the elements and actions performed on the Photos fxml page.

    Jahnavi Bavuluri and Chiraag Rekhari

      This method allows a user to copy the displayed photo into another album but both the photo is not removed from the current album.

      This method deleted a tag from the displayed photo in the right side display panel.

      This method allows a user to edit a caption on the currently displayed photo.
      void logout()
      This method takes the user back to the albums screen where they can choose to view another album.
      void movePhoto()
      This method allows the user to move the displayed photo from the current album to another existing album -- the photo is removed from the current album.

      This method deletes all the photo views (gridpanes) and calls the start method to repopulate the photo views in the album.
      void start​(javafx.stage.Stage mainStage, int albumIndex, int userIndex)
      The start method displays all the photos in the selected album along with their captions.
      void viewSlideshow()
      This method handles the transition from this current photos view to the slideshow view so the user can view their photos in a slideshow manner.

      • resetPhotos

        public void resetPhotos()
                 throws java.lang.Exception
        This method deletes all the photo views (gridpanes) and calls the start method to repopulate the photo views in the album.

        This method is called whenever an edit is made so this change can be reflected in all the photos and the display panel can also be updated.

        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
